        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 21 at 11:48PM CDT by NWS Memphis TN</headline>
        <description>At 1148 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Egypt, or 7 miles west of Bono, moving southeast at 45 mph.

HAZARD...Half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor hail damage to vegetation is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Hergett, Needham, Apt, Herman, Valley View, Egypt, Dryden, Cash,
Farrville, Greenfield, Dorothy, Bono, Craighead Forest Park,
Winesburg, Jonesboro, Gilkerson, Otwell, Cary, Lanieve, and Herndon.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
